3.20.20  10:56 am   With the coronavirus pandemic worsening, I can relate to this quote from "a Play":

"a theater needs to have seats, a stage, and a box office. a theatre can be anywhere, or anything"

Thanks to that line, I can be assured that my home is a theatre where I can watch movies that were in theaters or scheduled for a theatrical release around the time the contagion intensified early on VOD and streaming services.

By mechanical pencil logic, is your home also a theatre, and are you also ready to watch movies in your theatre?
